title: RuntimeError: Expected numpy.ndarray of uint8
body:
THIS IS NOT TECH SUPPORT FOR NEWBIE FAKERS
POST ONLY ISSUES RELATED TO BUGS OR CODE

## Expected behavior

Using the new DeepFaceLabTorrent_build_15_02_2019 Windows prebuilt release, when running the batch job "5) data_dst extract faces DLIB best GPU.bat" I receive the error message below.

## Actual behavior

Error Message:

```
Running extractor.

Performing 1st pass...
Running on GeForce GTX 1080 Ti.
  0%|                                                                                         | 0/1107 [00:00<?, ?it/s]Exception while process data [D:\DeepFaceLabTorrent_build_15_02_2019\DeepFaceLabTorrent\workspace\data_dst\00001.png]: Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "D:\DeepFaceLabTorrent_build_15_02_2019\DeepFaceLabTorrent\_internal\bin\DeepFaceLab\utils\SubprocessorBase.py", line 243, in subprocess
    result = self.onClientProcessData (data)
  File "D:\DeepFaceLabTorrent_build_15_02_2019\DeepFaceLabTorrent\_internal\bin\DeepFaceLab\mainscripts\Extractor.py", line 304, in onClientProcessData
    rects = self.e.extract_from_bgr (image)
  File "D:\DeepFaceLabTorrent_build_15_02_2019\DeepFaceLabTorrent\_internal\bin\DeepFaceLab\facelib\DLIBExtractor.py", line 31, in extract_from_bgr
    detected_faces = self.dlib_cnn_face_detector(input_image, 0)
RuntimeError: Expected numpy.ndarray of uint8
```

## Steps to reproduce

Run extract jobs

## Other relevant information

Win10 x64, GTX 1080TI
Previous release (DeepFaceLabTorrent_build_07_02_2019) is working fine.
